history.content:
I'm not sure if you are EECS or CS. If you are EECS, your ESS advisor might contact you to remind you that you need to be enrolled in two techs, but I'm not sure.

In either case, if you do not think you will get into either waitlisted tech, you should plan for a backup. If it doesn't work out and you end up with only 1 tech, you'll want to work with an advisor to plan out your remaining semesters. You could even book an appointment with an advisor now so you have your plan ready before the rush of the semester begins.

I'm currently in enrolled in one technical, and wait-listed for two more. I am sufficiently high enough on the waitlist, that I am worried I won't get in to them. What happens if classes start and we're not enrolled in two technicals?

Also, how do we view our degree progress in cal central?

Thanks!
history.subject: Two Technical Requirement & DARS
